sourceDesc.p: These transcriptions and their accompanying images include at least one copy of all original versions of the Wandering Jew's Chronicle known to the editor at the time of publication, not including later reprints. A full description of the publishing history of the ballad and a bibliography of all currently located copies is given on the project website. Sources and other files are available at https://github.com/gbergel/WJC.

projectDesc.p: This project was funded by a British Academy Small Grant awarded to Dr. Giles Bergel. Full credits and a description of the project are available on the project website at.

editorialDecl.p: Transcriptions have been made along quasi-diplomatic lines, with the following exceptions.

hyphenation.p: Metrical lines have been restored without any hyphenation where lines have been broken in the original sources

normalization.p: The early-modern use of two 'v's has been mapped onto a modern 'w' character. Acute accents have been disregarded. Ligatures have not been retained. Roman (or 'whiteletter') characters used in a predominantly blackletter setting are rendered in italic, as are blackletter characters in a predominantly Roman setting (italics in the original are preserved). The long and short forms of 's' have been normalised.
